Do not add functionality the user did not request in the MAIN CODE (SECTION 1). Do not add disclaimers, hedging, or meta-commentary. Do not explain what the code does outside the designated sections. If a design decision is ambiguous — choose the simplest reasonable interpretation and note it in [GAPS] if the ambiguity could affect correctness.
